quran[3]{c,v,t}:
  62,9,"O believers, when proclamation is made for prayer on the Day of Congregation, hasten to God's remembrance and leave trafficking aside; that is better for you, did you but know"
  62,10,"Then, when the prayer is finished, scatter in the land and seek God's bounty, and remember God frequently; haply you will prosper"
  62,11,"But when they see merchandise or diversion they scatter off to it, and they leave thee standing. Say: 'What is with God is better than diversion and merchandise. God is the best of providers"